cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.SI, cs.CY 

The paper discusses the protection of consumer privacy and the management of huge amounts of data in Advanced Metering Infrastructure (AMI). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also proposes a new architecture that involves data buffering and modularization of utility grid analysis, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases). Additionally, the paper discusses the delivery of anonymized summary data, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
